  Trust the NUMA claim only on DRAMbnd rows (even partitions half-tree > L3).
  CONFOUND rows: partition fits L3 but naive does not -> any P/N<1 is a cache
    effect, NOT NUMA locality. cacheRes rows: NUMA irrelevant (all fits L3).
  spheres (compute-bound): R/N,P/N,H/N ~1.0 even on DRAMbnd rows.
  hairball (memory-bound): R/H<1 on DRAMbnd rows, more at dist32 = real NUMA.

